termine","different","display","documentation","domain","dryrun","each","endpoint","endpoints","event","events","events.prisoner.merged","events.prisoner.received","false","filter","following","for","formats","get","h1","has","have","held","hmpps","holding","identifier","identifiers","ids","implemented","important","in","independent","information","integrate","integrated","integration","interaction","interfaces","into","is","json","justice","likely","link","list","logic","long","managed","management","map","match","matches","matching","merged","message","moved","moves","must","need","new","nomis","noms","nomsnumbers","none","not","number","of","offender","on","once","openapi","order","other","over","parameterintyperequireddescription","parameters","period","person","personal","person’s","place","post","prison","prisoner","probation","process","processing","query","raised","received","record","recorded","records","reference","request","requests","required","responses","resulting","role","role_probation_api__prison_identifier__update","roles","schemas","secured","sentence","service","set","stages","status","statusdescriptionschema","supervision","supplied","support","swagger","system","systems","technical","that","the","these","this","through","time","to","triggered","triggers","true","two","type","ui","up","used","uses","using","v1.0","ways","we","when","will","with","workflow","workflows","yaml","yet"],"pipeline":["trimmer"]}, "docs": {"14":{"title":"About","content":"Prison Identifier and Delius\nBusiness Need\nHMPPS has a number of systems each holding information about a person’s interaction with different aspects of the justice system. These systems have been set up and managed over a long period of time resulting in different identifiers being used for a person in each. In order to integrate these independent systems we must match the person records using the information held in each. To achieve this for NOMIS (NOMS Number) and Delius (CRN) we query the two systems and determine that likely matches based on the data. Once we have a likely match we can link the records by adding the NOMS Number to the person record in the Delius database. When this link is in place the two systems can be integrated in other ways to support case management as the person moves through different stages of HMPPS supervision.\nContext Map\n\nWorkflow Triggers\nBatch Processing\nThe matching process can be triggered by a request to the integration service API endpoint\n\n        \n          \nBusiness Event\nAPI Endpoint\n\nList of CRNs to Match\n/person/match-by-crn\n\nList of NOMIS IDs to Match\n/person/match-by-noms\n\n        \n      Domain Event Processing\nThe matching process will be triggered by domain events raised by Delius, once these events are implemented\n\n        \n          \nBusiness Event\nMessage Event Type / Filter\nStatus\n\nNew Sentence Added to Delius\nprobation-case.sentence.created\nNot yet implemented\n\nSentence Changed in Delius\nprobation-case.sentence.amended\nNot yet implemented\n\nSentence Moved to New Delius Event\nprobation-case.sentence.move\nNot yet implemented\n\nPrisoner received into NOMIS\nprison-offender-events.prisoner.received\nActive\n\nPrisoner merged in NOMIS\nprison-offender-events.prisoner.merged\nActive\n\n        \n      Workflows\nBatch Processing\n\nInterfaces\nAPI Access Control\nAPI endpoints are secured by roles supplied by the HMPPS Auth client used in\nthe requests\n\n        \n          \nAPI Endpoint\nRequired Role\n\nAll\nROLE_PROBATION_API__PRISON_IDENTIFIER__UPDATE\n\n        \n      Concepts\nPerson Record Matching Process\nThe logic used to match NOMIS person records to Delius person records uses the basic personal details, any additional identifiers and the recorded sentence dates.\n\n","url":"/"},"15":{"title":"API Reference","content":"\n    \n    API Reference\n\n\n.technical-documentation \u003e h1 { display: none !important }\nThe following documentation is also available in these formats:\n\n\nOpenAPI JSON\nOpenAPI YAML\nSwagger UI\n\nAPI Reference v1.0\n\n\n\n\n\n\n/person/match-by-noms\n\nget\n\n\n\n\nParameters\n\n\nParameterInTypeRequiredDescription\n\n\n\n\ndryRun\nquery\nboolean\nfalse\n\n\n\n\n\n\nnomsNumbers\nquery\narray\ntrue\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nResponses\n\n\nStatusDescriptionSchema\n\n\n\n\n202\n\nAccepted\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\npost\n\n\n\n\nParameters\n\n\nParameterInTypeRequiredDescription\n\n\n\n\ndryRun\nquery\nboolean\nfalse\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nResponses\n\n\nStatusDescriptionSchema\n\n\n\n\n202\n\nAccepted\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n/person/match-by-crn\n\nget\n\n\n\n\nParameters\n\n\nParameterInTypeRequiredDescription\n\n\n\n\ndryRun\nquery\nboolean\nfalse\n\n\n\n\n\n\ncrns\nquery\narray\nfalse\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nResponses\n\n\nStatusDescriptionSchema\n\n\n\n\n202\n\nAccepted\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\npost\n\n\n\n\nParameters\n\n\nParameterInTypeRequiredDescription\n\n\n\n\ndryRun\nquery\nboolean\nfalse\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nResponses\n\n\nStatusDescriptionSchema\n\n\n\n\n202\n\nAccepted\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nSchemas\n\n","url":"/api-reference.html"}}}